Project: Atlantic Shores OWF Geotechnical SI 2022 - HOS Browning
Activity Description:
Port call activities:
•	The drilling crew rigs up for CDS load and deployment tests
•	General maintenance to drilling equipment
•	During positioning of the LARS for load testing the top synthetic wear plate above the snubber locks broke 
•	Replace wear plate
•	Start crane ops to load drilling mud and supplies. Operations stopped due to strong winds
•	Waiting on winds to subside to continue the loading operations
•	ASOW reps embark 
•	The drilling crew conducts load cell calibration for CDS load and deployment tests
•	At 1530H, while derigging the lifting arrangement configuration after calibrating the load cell, the spearhead was overpulled into the snubber while the LARS was boomed out and the cable did not have enough slack, breaking the synthetic wear inner rings scattering some small pieces over the deck
•	Remove spearhead from snubber
•	Start replacement of broken parts

Project: CMP - Geotechnical Studies - El Romeral Mine
Activity Description:
SA-03
Durante el ensayo, el agua se filtra por la columna HWT y aflora en superficie. Esto debido al bypass inducido por el agrietamiento o rompimiento del suelo al instalar el packer (suelo de muy baja resistencia para el ensayo). Se comprueba el buen estado de los packer, se realizan pruebas de packer y conexiones. Se decide avanzar con la perforación hasta 75 m, y volver a evaluar la ejecución de Ensayo Lefranc o Lugeon.

Project: ONE-Dyas BV Platform & Pipeline IRM Campaign
Activity Description:
Reconfiguring of TSS660E system to try and reduce noise/interference to coils/system from thrusters/power
Numerous attempts to alter set-up and tests carried out in harbour
Mounted SEP on top of ROV and trialled - same tests as carried out on previous occasions: background compensations and running thrusters at various speeds, altering signal threshold - results look promising, ST reduced back to recommended levels, noise/interference not evident
Ballast checks of system in new configuration
ROV put back in vessel
